email i just got... "Aaron,
New York Sen. Chuck Schumer is refusing to meet with his constituents to hear their concerns about the internet censorship bill, PIPA. As a staffer in his office recently told one of our members, they "don't care about this issue," and they are not willing to schedule meetings about it.
Click here right now to request a meeting with Schumer.
If you have already tried to request a meeting with Chuck, call his office now to follow up:
Call Schumer's office at 212-486-4430
Schumer, a co-sponsor of PIPA, and he has taken $2.6 million from the corporations that support the bill in this year alone. Now he needs to hear from the people of New York that they will not accept a censored internet and that they will hold him accountable if he votes in favor.
The goal right now is to get meetings set. Once we have a meeting secured, we'll get small groups organized and get you the materials you need to make the meeting go off smoothly. But for this first step it's important that Schumer hears from as many New York residents as possible. He wants to avoid talking to us. Our job right now is to make that impossible.
One last thing: please use this Facebook share button to help spread the message:
 
Thank You!
-Donny Shaw"

With over 80 years... in operation, Los Angeles International Airport (LAX) is the world's sixth busiest airport for number of passengers and 13th in tonnage of air cargo handled. LAX strives for excellence in serving the evolving needs of the community and visitors who frequent this diverse metropolitan hub.

The central complex features nine passenger terminals connected by a U-shaped two-level roadway. Curbside baggage check-in is available on the upper departure level. Baggage claim is on the lower level. Brand-named and ethnic-styled restaurants, cocktail lounges, gift shops, newsstands, duty free shops for international flights, restrooms, public telephones and business centers offer convenient services for the traveling public.

Other amenities include a first aid station in the Tom Bradley International Terminal and special telephones connected to area hotels/motels, bus/limousine services and car rental firms serving most Southland communities. Free shuttle service is provided between all terminals and remote parking lots.

message:
Hey everyone,
Thanks for helping me out with my other hotel's Facebook page. We need a few more people to like the Holiday Inn Dulles Airport too so it'd be great if you can help out.

Let me know if you have a Facebook page you need more likes for and I'll help you out in return for liking ours!

Thanks in advance for the help!
description:
One of Washington’s best hotels, the Holiday Inn Washington Dulles International Airport provides lodging accommodations in Northern Virginia near Washington Dulles International Airport and 25 miles from Washington D.C. Holiday Inn Dulles Airport is convenient to Dulles 28 Centre where Wegmans and Target are located, Dulles Town Center Mall, Leesburg Corner Premium Outlets, Ashburn, DC's Wine Country, Civil War Sites, and W&OD Railroad and Bike Trail. We are positioned near the new National Air and Space Museum Dulles Annex - Steven F. Udvar-Hazy Center.

Local businesses include AOL/Time Warner, WorldCom, FAA, SAIC, AIBS, ADESA, DTRA, USGS, Howard Hughes Medical Institute, NIMA, EDS, Raytheon, Exxon/Mobil, Deloitte, Lockheed Martin, GeoLogistics Americas, Verizon, United Airlines, Rockwell Collins and Northrop Grumman.

When traveling to Washington make the Holiday Inn Washington Dulles Airport your first choice for Washington hotels.
